    • Field Detail

      • routeName

        public final java.lang.String routeName
        The name of the route. Note: This cannot contain whitespace characters (ie spaces, tabs, or new lines), as its used in a url.

      • color

        public int color
        The color of the route. This is optional, as there is a high chance that the route does not have one.

        This is an int instead of a Color object as android stores its colors as an integer.

      • stops

        public Stop[] stops
        The array of stops for this route. This may be empty / null if the route has not been initialized, and the stops haven't been loaded.

      • polyLineCoordinates

        public com.google.android.gms.maps.model.LatLng[] polyLineCoordinates
        The array of LatLng coordinates that will be used to create the polyline (if enabled).

      • enabled

        public boolean enabled
        Whether or not the route is enabled or disabled (to be shown or hidden). Default is false (disabled).

      • EMPTY_ROUTE

        public static final Route[] EMPTY_ROUTE
        Fallback empty route array used as a way to circumvent potential exceptions.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Route

        public Route(@NonNull
             java.lang.String routeName)
      throws Route.RouteException
        Constructor for the route. The name of the route is the only thing that is required. Be sure that the provided route name does NOT contain any whitespace characters!
        Parameters:
        routeName - The name of the route. Be sure this does NOT contain any whitespace characters!
        Throws:
        Route.RouteException - Thrown if the route name contains white space characters.

      • Route

        public Route(java.lang.String routeName,
             int color)
      throws Route.RouteException
        Constructor for the route. The name of the route is the only thing that is required. Be sure that the provided route name does NOT contain any whitespace characters!
        Parameters:
        routeName - The name of the route. Be sure this does NOT contain any whitespace characters!
        color - The route's color. This is optional, and of the color is non-existent simply use the Route(String routeName) constructor.
        Throws:
        Route.RouteException - Thrown if the route name contains white space characters.

    • Method Detail

      • generateRoutes

        @NonNull
public static Route[] generateRoutes(org.json.JSONArray masterSchedule)
        Generates the array of routes from the master schedule json array. If a null array is provided then an empty array will be returned.
        Parameters:
        masterSchedule - The json array containing the master schedule containing all the routes.
        Returns:
        The routes derived from the master schedule.

      • enableFavoriteRoutes

        public static void enableFavoriteRoutes(Route[] favoritedRoutes)
        Iterates though all the routes in MapsActivity.allRoutes and enables those that have been favorited (as determined by being in the favoritedRoutes array).

        This should only be run once.

        Parameters:
        favoritedRoutes - The selected routes to be enabled from MapsActivity.allRoutes.

      • loadStops

        public Stop[] loadStops()
        Retrieves and parses the stops for the given route. This function does not apply the stops the route.
        Returns:
        The array stops corresponding the route.

      • loadPolyLineCoordinates

        public void loadPolyLineCoordinates()
                             throws org.json.JSONException
        Loads the polyline coordinates for the route object by retrieving the array from the RouteMatch server. This method will either set the polyline coordinates for the route, or will return early if the route match object is null.
        Throws:
        org.json.JSONException - Thrown if there is an issue parsing the polyline coordinates from the returned json.

      • getPolyline

        public com.google.android.gms.maps.model.Polyline getPolyline()
        Returns the polyline that corresponds to the route.
        Returns:
        The polyline that corresponds to the route.

      • createPolyline

        @UiThread
public void createPolyline()
        Creates and sets the polyline for the route. If there are no polyline coordinates for the route then this simply returns early and does not create the polyline.

      • addSharedStop

        public void addSharedStop(SharedStop sharedStop)
        Adds the shared to the routes shared stop array.
        Parameters:
        sharedStop - The shared stop to add to the route.

      • getSharedStops

        @Nullable
public SharedStop[] getSharedStops()
        Gets the shared stops for the route. This may be null if there are none.
        Returns:
        The shared stops for the route.

      • removePolyline

        @UiThread
public void removePolyline()
        Removes the routes polyline from the map, and sets it to null. This must be run on the UI thread.
